</tr></tbody>
</table>
</clause>

<clause id="_examples_2" obligation="normative">
<title>Examples</title>
<p id="_7564ca56-8cbc-375f-5cb6-9e9910a9a886">The following is an example of a response to an OGC API — Records query operation (path: <tt>/collections/{collectionId}/items</tt>).  This example shows a JSON response and the response container is a GeoJSON feature collection.  Specific records are not presented in this example to illustrate the structure of the response container in GeoJSON.</p>

<sourcecode id="records-example" lang="json"><name>Records Example in GeoJSON</name>{
  "type": "FeatureCollection",
  "timeStamp": "2021-03-06T07:10:00Z",
  "numberReturned": 10,
  "numberMatched": 347,
  "features": [
     { ... record ... },
     { ... record ... },
     { ... record ... },
     { ... record ... },
     { ... record ... },
     .
     .
     .
  ],
  "links": [
    {
       "href": "https://www.someserver.com/ogcapi/collections/tepcat?f=json...",
       "rel": "collection",
       "type": "application/geo+json",
       "title": "Link to the containing collection in JSON"
    },
    {
       "href": "https://www.someserver.com/ogcapi/collections/tepcat?f=html...",
       "rel": "collection",
       "type": "text/html",
       "title": "Link to the containing collection in HTML"
    },
    {
       "href": "https://www.someserver.com/ogcapi/collections/tepcat/items?f=json&amp;...",
       "rel": "self",
       "type": "application/geo+json",
       "title": "Link to this response"
    },
    {
       "href": "https://www.someserver.com/ogcapi/collections/tepcat/items?f=html&amp;...",
       "rel": "alternate",
       "type": "text/html",
       "title": "Link to this response in HTML"
    },
    {
