<p id="_aad65448-e562-ab1e-7fa4-dfc17303d42f">In practice the responsible standard would define how the two sets of properties are merged into the local resources item.  In this case it is straight forward since the collection object (path: <tt>/collections/{collectionID}</tt>) and the record share a large number of properties.  Where there is a difference, <tt>extent</tt> versus <tt>geometry</tt> and <tt>time</tt>, can be handled by including both sets of properties in the local resources item and ensuring that their values are consistent.</p>
</clause>

<clause id="_examples_5" obligation="normative">
<title>Examples</title>
<clause id="_collections_example" obligation="normative">
<title>Collections example</title>
<p id="_3d1d5ea0-0d14-517e-393b-0b732f3658d3">The following JSON Schema fragments illustrate how to extended the <link target="https://docs.ogc.org/is/17-069r4/17-069r4.html#_collections_">collections object</link> (a local resources catalog) and the <link target="https://docs.ogc.org/is/17-069r4/17-069r4.html#_collection_">collection object</link> (a local resources item) to include properties required and recommended by this requirements class.</p>

